longBusinessSummary: C-Com Satellite Systems Inc. develops and deploys commercial grade mobile auto-deploying satellite-based technology for the delivery of two-way high-speed Internet, VoIP, and video services into vehicles. The company offers iNetVu, a proprietary mobile auto-deploying antenna for the delivery of satellite based Internet services into vehicles while stationary virtually anywhere one can drive, as well as for the transportable platforms. It also provides driveaway, flyaway, and fixed motorized antennas. In addition, the company offers accessories, such as powersmart products, beacon receivers, transportable cases, cables, transportable enclosed skids, and custom integrations, as well as antenna controllers. Its products and services deliver solutions for fixed and mobile applications. The company serves oil and gas exploration, military, communications, disaster management, emergency responders, broadcasters, telemedicine, mobile education and office, government, banking, and other sectors. The company operates in Canada, the United States, Asia, the Russian Federation, Europe, and internationally. C-Com Satellite Systems Inc. was incorporated in 1997 and is headquartered in Ottawa, Canada.
